  1. Compute the median alcohol content and international bitterness unit for each state. Plot a bar chart to compare.
# Median ABV & IBU
median_abv_ibu <- beer_brew %>% 
  filter(state != "DC") %>% 
  group_by(state) %>% 
  summarise(median_abv = median(abv, na.rm = TRUE),
            median_ibu = median(ibu, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  rename(st = state) %>% 
  mutate(state = tolower(state.name[match(st,state.abb)]),
         highlight_abv = (max(median_abv) == median_abv),
         highlight_ibu = (max(median_ibu, na.rm = TRUE) == median_ibu)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = c(2:3), names_to = "measure")
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)
# MB comment: we should brainstorm how to better present this as a bar chart
ggplot() +
  geom_col(data = median_abv_ibu, aes(value, state, fill = measure)) +
  geom_col(data = subset(median_abv_ibu, highlight_abv == TRUE),
           aes(value, state), fill = c("black", NA)) +
  geom_col(data = subset(median_abv_ibu, highlight_ibu == TRUE),
           aes(value, state), fill = c(NA, "black")) +
  facet_wrap( ~ measure, scales = "free_x") +
  labs(title = "Median ABV & IBU by State",
       fill = "") +
  theme_minimal() +
  guides(fill = FALSE) +
  NULL
